      <encodingDesc><p>Restored pulli and long ē/ō which are not differentiated in the manuscript. Metrical word-split made in the appropriate sections. Sandhi retained in all cases and word-split made where possible in the prose commentary. No word-split when there is overshort u-sandhi or final/initial m-sandhi. Glides retained and added to the beginning of the latter word.   The is only one punctuation mark in the MS. I have rendered it as a full stop in all cases.</p></encodingDesc>
      
